<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="720" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">121.893/8–146: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to
                                General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-01">August 1, 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>WH 489. Receipt of your message of July 30 is acknowledged.</p>
                        <p>I appreciate your difficulties, approve of the method you are following,
                            and hope with you for success in accomplishing a peaceful solution of
                            the Chinese problem.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>